{
  "stem": "15396.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But partly, the unfairness, the-- the unreasonable, unreasonably unfairness of it was what was so-- Some of the pillars of the-- I mean, the people who were contributing more to-- well, certainly, to art, and music, and all that.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the-- the people who were real citizens, some of the ones that I would have admired the most happened to have been Jewish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was all by accident.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It wasn't any choice or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It just happened to be that way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Vaguely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not-- not knowing what to do, and doing anything that-- I had two or three friends who were telling me-- that's how I started finding out about girls.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you would marry them, they could get papers to go to-- to the consulate.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Had to be careful that, you know, they didn't have communications the way they do today.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they-- you had to go to a different consulate every time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Otherwise, there'd be 15 Mrs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Charles Fawcetts.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I had quite a story with that later on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that and making-- we made a couple false papers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I stole a couple of sheets of stationery one time from-- from the consulate, and we wrote in some very strange things about a couple who were supposed to be Americans, and they weren't at all.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they took it to wherever-- to the-- the, I guess, whoever's in charge of-- of immigration at that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I think they got papers, you know, more papers, and then those disappeared, of course.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But through that, they got other papers, and the first thing you know, the American consulate in Antwerp really thought that they were Americans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was completely false.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
